{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Wood"], "type": "title", "extent": [59, 68], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [68, 104], "text": ["Simulates shiny wood grain."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [104, 147], "text": ["This operator simulates shiny wood grain."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [147, 307], "text": ["The Vein Frequency (", {"text": ["vfreq"], "type": "code"}, ") input controls the number of veins in the\npattern. For veins that fade out gradually, vary the Vein Attenuation\n(", {"text": ["vatten"], "type": "code"}, ") input."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [307, 640], "text": ["The Vein Scale (", {"text": ["vscale"], "type": "code"}, ") input offers a good means of controlling the\nellipse ratio of the veins. Thus, tree stumps, which have rings of a\nfairly circular nature, should use a ", {"text": ["vscale"], "type": "code"}, " value close to one.\nLongitudinal cross-sections, on the other hand, are very elliptical and\nshould use a ", {"text": ["vscale"], "type": "code"}, " value greater or less than one."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [640, 883], "text": ["The Groove Depth (", {"text": ["gdepth"], "type": "code"}, ") input allows you to displace the surface along\nthe vein area. A groove depth of zero will not generate any\ndisplacements at all. Alternatively, you can use the Vein Amount output\nin a separate displacement shader."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [883, 1055], "text": ["This operator uses the Ripples pattern as the vein generator. Other\ntechniques include using the Veins operator with a cylindrical\nprojection and one-sided vein softness."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1055, 1656], "text": ["If the Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, "), Normal (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") and texture coordinate (s t) inputs are\nnot connected, the global variables by the same names will be used\ninstead. Typically, you will use ", {"text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as\ninputs for ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ", and Shading Layer Parameter as the input for ", {"text": ["s"], "type": "code"}, " and\n", {"text": ["t"], "type": "code"}, ". You will not touch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you want to apply additional\ndisplacement to the wood surface using an operator such as ", {"text": ["Bump Map"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap"}, ". If you need to access the global variables directly, they are\navailable from the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1665, 1689], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1689, 1709], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/marble", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/marble"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1709, 1730], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/ripples", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/ripples"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1730, 1756], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shadinglayer", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/shadinglayer"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1756, 1775], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/veins", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/veins"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1775, 1799], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/woodplank", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/woodplank"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1656, 1665], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates shiny wood grain."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "wood", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/wood"}, "title": ["Wood"]}